s, and premium amenities, offering a unique living experience in Noida.\"\r\n          }\r\n        },\r\n        {\r\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n          \"name\": \"Are there luxury apartments in Sector 107 Noida at Sharanam?\",\r\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n            \"text\": \"Yes, Sharanam offers luxury apartments in Sector 107 Noida with spacious designs, high-end finishes, and landscaped surroundings.\"\r\n          }\r\n        },\r\n        {\r\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n          \"name\": \"What types of apartments are available at Sharanam?\",\r\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n            \"text\": \"The project offers 3 BHK and 4 BHK apartments designed for comfort, privacy, and modern urban living.\"\r\n          }\r\n        },\r\n        {\r\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n          \"name\": \"What amenities are available at Great Value Sharanam?\",\r\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n            \"text\": \"Amenities include landscaped gardens, clubhouse, swimming pool, 24/7 security, and dedicated parking.\"\r\n          }\r\n        },\r\n        {\r\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\r\n          \"name\": \"Where is Great Value Sharanam located?\",\r\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\r\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\r\n            \"text\": \"Sharanam is located in Sector 107, Noida, providing excellent connectivity to Noida Expressway, Delhi NCR, schools, hospitals, and shopping centers.\"\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n      ]\r\n    }\r\n  ]\r\n}',1,'2025-06-30 06:49:22','2026-01-13 07:25:11',NULL),(30,'oc-in-real-estate','What is an OC (Occupancy Certificate) & Its Importance?','blog/1752062054_desk_webp','OC in Real Estate','blog/1752062054_thumb_webp','blog/1752062054_desk_jpeg','blog/1752062054_thumb_jpg','<p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">In real estate, legal documents play a central role in guaranteeing that property ownership is valid and protected. An example of such an important document is the Occupancy Certificate (OC), which serves as the primary document for verifying whether a building is safe and compliant with relevant regulations. Lacking it, a transaction of a property can be very risky and jeopardise an investment.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">This blog explores why obtaining an OC is crucial for property buyers and owners. We will discuss how it secures your investment, the legal basis for not having it, and the necessary steps to ensure you meet the legal requirements when transacting real estate.</span></p><p><br></p><h2><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">What is an Occupancy Certificate?</span></h2><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">An Occupancy Certificate is a governmental document issued by local municipal authorities certifying that a building is suitable for occupation. It is evident that the </span><a href=\"https://greatvaluerealty.com/residential-properties-ncr\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent;\">residential property</a><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\"> has been developed in accordance with the sanctioned plans and meets the applicable safety, structural, and legal standards. Only after an inspection does the municipal authority release the OC, verifying that the building complies with the current regulations and is not plagued by any issues of safety.</span></p><p><br></p><h2><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">Major Features of an Occupancy Certificate</span></h2><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">Safety Compliance:</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\"> The OC ensures that the building meets all essential safety standards, including fire safety provisions, structural soundness, and compliance with local building codes and regulations.</span></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">Legality: </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">This certificate is a legal requirement, declaring a building to be approved for occupancy. Without one, the property will be deemed illegal for occupation.</span></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">Building Plan Approval: </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">The OC ensures that construction has taken place by the sanctioned building plans, without deviation or change.</span></p><p><br></p><h2><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">Why is an Occupancy Certificate Imperative?</span></h2><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">1. Legal Requirement</strong></h3><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">In most areas, it is a non-negotiable condition to get an OC before legally occupying a newly built or redeveloped property. If your </span><a href=\"https://greatvaluerealty.com/blog/flats-vs-apartments\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent;\">flat or apartment</a><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\"> is not OC certified, you may face legal actions, penalties or forced eviction.</span></p><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">2. Ensures Safety</strong></h3><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">One of the primary responsibilities of the OC is to ensure that the property meets the safety standards for its occupants. This involves verifying the structural integrity of the building, providing fire safety provisions, and adhering to other regulations that guarantee the security and safety of the residents.</span></p><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">3. Utility Connections</strong></h3><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">A copy of an OC is usually required to link integral facilities such as electricity, water, and sewage. Those who provide these facilities will request a copy of the OC before establishing services, making it a crucial step in the process.</span></p><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">4. Aids in Property Transfers</strong></h3><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">If you are selling or buying a property, the OC is essential. It attests that the structure is lawfully built, facilitating the process of obtaining financing or insurance. Without the OC, any transaction related to the property becomes complex and may take time, resulting in delays. This is one of the </span><a href=\"https://greatvaluerealty.com/blog/common-mistakes-to-avoid-while-buying-properties-for-sale-in-noida\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: transparent;\">common mistakes made by buyers</a><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\"> or sellers when purchasing a property.</span></p><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">5. Financial Approval</strong></h3><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">For homebuyers in need of a home loan, having an OC is a significant requirement. The lender applies the certificate to ensure the property is valid and secure, which is essential when obtaining a mortgage or home loan.</span></p><p><br></p><h2><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">How to Check the Validity of an Occupancy Certificate</span></h2><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">To examine an OC is a vital process, most importantly for potential buyers and investors. Here are some ways to do it:</span></p><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">Contact Local Authorities</strong></h3><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">You need to contact the local municipal or building authority that issued the OC. They can verify the authenticity of the certificate and confirm whether it is genuine or not.</span></p><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">Examine the Document</strong></h3><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">You need to carefully review the details in OC, such as the name of the authority, the date it was issued, and the property\'s address. Cross-check these details with the property records to ensure consistency.</span></p><p><br></p><h3><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">Use Online Verification Tools</strong></h3><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">In other areas, the local authorities offer online verification services. You can easily check the certificate\'s validity by entering the OC number or property details on these websites.</span></p><p><br></p><h2><strong style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">Conclusion</strong></h2><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">An Occupancy Certificate is more than a mere document—it\'s a building block of real estate transactions that confirms buildings are safe, legal, and fit for occupation. If you are an investor, buyer, or developer, it is essential to understand the importance of OC to avoid potential legal complications. Always check that the property you are buying has a proper and valid OC. This will not only bring peace of mind but also serve as a security certificate for your family or those who will occupy the space.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(14, 16, 26); background-color: transparent;\">Properties of Great Value Realty always prioritise the safety of its residents. With a comprehensive understanding of the OC\'s role in real estate, they ensure consistency with legal and safety standards, keeping your property transactions safe and secure.</span></p>','2025-07-04','What is an Occupancy Certificate (OC) & Why is it Important in Real Estate?','null','Learn about the significance of an Occupancy Certificate (OC) in real estate. Understand how this essential legal document ensures safety, legality, and compliance for property owners and buyers.','What is an Occupancy Certificate (OC) & Why is it Important in Real Estate?','\"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\r\n  \"@graph\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"@type\": \"BlogPosting\",\r\n      \"@id\": \"https://greatvaluerealty.com/blog/oc-in-real-estate#blogpost\",\r\n      \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\r\n        \"@type\": \"WebPage\",\r\n        \"@id\": \"https://greatvaluerealty.com/blog/oc-in-real-estate\"\r\n      },\r\n      \"headline\": \"Understanding OC in Real Estate\",\r\n      \"description\": \"Learn about the importance of an Occupancy Certificate (OC) in real estate, its role in property legality, and why it\'s essential for buyers.\",\r\n      \"image\": \"https://greatvaluerealty.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/oc-in-real-estate.jpg\",\r\n      \"author\": {\r\n        \"@type\": \"Organization\",\r\n        \"name\": \"Great Value Realty\"\r\n      },\r\n      \"publisher\": {\r\n        \"@type\": \"Organization\",\r\n        \"name\": \"Great Value Realty\",\r\n        \"logo\": {\r\n          \"@type\": \"ImageObject\",\r\n     