arby metro stations, and existing infrastructure, making it ideal for long-term residents and investors. The project\'s location offers both tranquillity and easy access to key parts of Noida.','2026-01-21 10:38:47','2026-01-21 10:38:47'),(209,55,'How does the construction quality of Ekanam compare to other Sector 107 projects?','Ekanam focuses on sustainable construction, with features such as green building standards and energy-efficient systems, which may not be as heavily emphasised in other projects. The design prioritizes long-term durability and comfort.','2026-01-21 10:39:01','2026-01-21 10:39:01'),(210,55,'Is Ekanam a good long-term investment compared to other projects in the area?','Yes, Ekanam’s exclusive design, low-density layout, and high-end facilities make it a strong candidate for long-term appreciation. Compared to more densely packed projects, it is expected to retain higher demand and value over time, making it a safer investment.','2026-01-21 10:39:17','2026-01-21 10:39:17'),(211,55,'How does Ekanam address sustainability compared to other projects in Sector 107?','Ekanam incorporates eco-friendly construction practices, including rainwater harvesting systems, solar panels, and energy-efficient designs, setting it apart from many other local developments that may lack a more robust sustainability focus.','2026-01-21 10:39:33','2026-01-21 10:39:33'),(212,56,'What are the most important factors to consider before investing in a residential property in Noida?','Consider your budget & financing, location & connectivity, builder credibility, legal compliance (RERA and documents), future infrastructure growth, and amenities offered by the project.','2026-01-22 11:51:01','2026-01-22 11:51:01'),(213,56,'What is the best location in Noida for residential investment?','Look at factors such as metro connectivity, proximity to workplaces and highways, neighbourhood demand, planned infrastructure, and the sector\'s growth prospects.','2026-01-22 11:51:22','2026-01-22 11:51:22'),(214,56,'Is Noida a good city for residential property investment in 2026?','Yes, due to its strategic location near Delhi, expanding infrastructure, strong connectivity, and ongoing urban development projects are driving demand and price growth.','2026-01-22 11:51:47','2026-01-22 11:51:47'),(215,56,'Why is RERA registration important when buying a residential property in Noida?','RERA registration ensures legal protection, transparency in project approvals, timelines, and the builder\'s accountability — reducing the risk of delays or disputes.','2026-01-22 11:52:05','2026-01-22 11:52:05'),(216,56,'How to choose the best location in Noida for residential investment?','Look at factors such as metro connectivity, proximity to workplaces and highways, neighbourhood demand, planned infrastructure, and the sector\'s growth prospects.','2026-01-22 11:52:20','2026-01-22 11:52:20'),(217,57,'How can RERA approval benefit buyers in Noida?','RERA approval ensures that the project is legally registered and complies with the required standards, giving buyers peace of mind about project legitimacy, quality construction, and on-time delivery.','2026-01-24 11:11:01','2026-01-24 11:11:01'),(218,57,'What happens if a RERA-approved project is delayed in Noida?','RERA mandates builders to deliver projects on time. In the event of delays, builders are liable to compensate buyers for the delay, thereby providing financial protection for investors.','2026-01-24 11:11:14','2026-01-24 11:11:14'),(219,57,'How do I check if a project in Noida is RERA approved?','You can verify a project’s RERA approval status by visiting the official UP-RERA website and searching with the project name or registration number.','2026-01-24 11:11:29','2026-01-24 11:11:29'),(220,57,'Are all real estate developers in Noida required to register with RERA?','Yes, as per the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016, all real estate developers must register their projects with RERA before advertising or selling.','2026-01-24 11:11:43','2026-01-24 11:11:43'),(221,57,'What are the risks of investing in non-RERA projects in Noida?','Non-RERA projects carry significant risks, including delayed possession, unregulated construction quality, and limited legal recourse in the event of disputes.','2026-01-24 11:12:06','2026-01-24 11:12:06'),(222,58,'Why is there a sudden shift towards buying 4 BHK apartments in Noida?','Post-pandemic, the definition of \"luxury\" has shifted from just \"premium finishes\" to \"extra space.\" Homebuyers are now prioritizing a dedicated Work-From-Home (WFH) office, a study room for kids, or a private guest room for elderly parents. A 4 BHK offers this flexibility without compromising the living room size.','2026-01-27 06:02:01','2026-01-27 06:02:01'),(223,58,'Which sectors in Noida are currently best for luxury real estate investment?','Sector 107 is emerging as the \"Goldilocks zone\": it is close to the Noida Expressway but away from highway noise. It offers excellent connectivity to Delhi via the Kalindi Kunj flyover and is surrounded by low-density developments.','2026-01-27 06:02:29','2026-01-27 06:02:29'),(224,58,'How does the upcoming Jewar Airport impact the resale value of 4 BHK flats in Noida?','The Noida International Airport (Jewar) is a massive catalyst. It has already pushed property prices up by 15-20% in sectors along the Expressway. Large-format homes (4 BHKs) are expected to see the highest appreciation, as they appeal to the influx of CXOs, expats, and senior executives working in nearby industrial hubs.','2026-01-27 06:02:44','2026-01-27 06:02:44'),(225,58,'Is it better to buy a bare-shell apartment or a fully fitted one?','Most luxury buyers today prefer fitted homes to avoid the hassle of civil work. Look for developers providing modular kitchens (with hobs/chimneys), Italian marble flooring, and fitted wardrobes. It saves 6-8 months of interior work time. Ekanam by Great Value Realty, for example, delivers units with high-end features such as imported marble and fully fitted German modular kitchens, enabling a quicker, stress-free move-in.','2026-01-27 06:03:01','2026-01-27 06:03:01'),(226,58,'What defines \"Ultra-Luxury\" in Noida\'s current market?','In 2026, \"Luxury\" isn\'t just about a swimming pool; it’s about Low Density and Smart Living. Buyers are rejecting crowded high-rises in favor of projects with fewer families per acre. Ultra-luxury now implies VRV air-conditioning, home automation, and exclusive amenities like infinity pools.','2026-01-27 06:03:48','2026-01-27 06:03:48'),(227,59,'What are the best real estate investment strategies for 2026?','Investors increasingly prioritise cash‑flow‑positive rental properties, value‑add improvements, and conservative financing in 2026’s market environment.','2026-02-05 07:03:45','2026-02-05 07:03:45'),(228,59,'Is real estate still a good investment in 2026?','Yes, real estate remains attractive due to stable rental income, long‑term capital appreciation, and inflation hedging, even in a slower‑growth environment.','2026-02-05 07:04:24','2026-02-05 07:04:24'),(229,59,'What are the key trends shaping real estate investment in 2026','Trends include technology and data analytics for investment decisions, evolving ownership models like fractional investments, and a deeper understanding of market cycles.','2026-02-05 07:05:01','2026-02-05 07:05:01'),(230,59,'What is the outlook for real estate investors in 2026?','The industry outlook indicates stable growth, driven by continued housing demand, mortgage activity, and demographic shifts.','2026-02-05 07:05:20','2026-02-05 07:05:20'),(231,59,'What is the BRRRR method, and how does it work?','BRRRR stands for Buy, Rehab, Rent, Refinance, Repeat — a strategy that helps scale rental portfolios by recycling capital.','2026-02-05 07:05:42','2026-02-05 07:05:42'),(232,60,'Is indexation still available for the property I inherited in 2025?','Yes, for properties acquired before July 23, 2024, you can choose between the 12.5% rate (no indexation) or the 20% rate (with indexation).','2026-02-09 07:00:44','2026-02-09 07:00:44'),(233,60,'How do I claim the 2026 \'Green Building\' tax rebate?','Many municipal bodies now offer a 5-10% property tax discount for buildings with certified solar, waste-management, or rainwater-harvesting systems.','2026-02-09 07:00:59','2026-02-09 07:00:59'),(234,60,'Can I still deduct ₹2 lakh in home loan interest under the New Tax Regime?','No, the ₹2 lakh interest deduction under Section 24(b) for self-occupied homes remains available only under the Old Tax Regime.','2026-02-09 07:02:57','2026-02-09 07:02:57'),(235,60,'What is the 2026 \'Black Money\' amnesty window for property?','The government has opened a one-time 6-month window to disclose foreign assets (including real estate) to avoid heavy penalties under the Black Money Act.','2026-02-09 07:03:15','2026-02-09 07:03:15'),(236,60,'Are there special tax breaks for \'City Economic Regions\' in 2026?','Properties in newly designated Tier-2/3 economic hubs may benefit from faster infrastructure development funded by the government’s ₹1.5 lakh crore interest-free loan pool.','2026-02-09 07:03:58','2026-02-09 07:03:58'),(237,61,'Is Noida better than Gurgaon for property investment?','Both cities offer strong investment potential. Noida is known for better infrastructure planning, wider roads, and relatively affordable pricing, while Gurgaon offers premium developments, strong corporate presence, and higher rental demand.','2026-02-17 05:45:21','2026-02-17 05:45:21'),(238,61,'Which location has better infrastructure: Noida or Gurgaon?','Noida is often praised for its planned infrastructure and metro connectivity. Gurgaon has strong road connectivity and proximity to the IGI Airport, but faces traffic congestion in certain areas.','2026-02-17 05:45:34','2026-02-17 05:45:34'),(239,61,'Is Noida safer than Gurgaon to live in?','Noida is generally considered safer and more systematically planned. However, safety varies by sector in both cities.','2026-02-17 05:45:48','2026-02-17 05:45:48'),(240,61,'Is Noida a good investment for long-term growth?','Yes. With infrastructure projects such as the Noida International Airport (Jewar Airport), Film City, and expanding metro networks, Noida demonstrates strong long-term growth potential.','2026-02-17 05:46:05','2026-02-17 05:46:05'),(241,61,'Noida vs Gurgaon: Which is better for end-users?','If affordability and planned living matter more, Noida may be ideal. If proximity to corporate hubs and a luxury lifestyle are priorities, Gurgaon may be the preferred choice.','2026-02-17 05:46:32','2026-02-17 05:46:32'),(242,62,'How much appreciation can I expect on Noida Expressway?','With the Jewar Airport nearing full operational capacity in 2026, properties along the Expressway have seen a CAGR of 10-15%. Projects near the upcoming Metro extensions show the highest potential.','2026-02-23 10:19:32','2026-02-23 10:19:32'),(243,62,'How does the Jewar Airport impact 3 BHK investments?','The 2026 operational status of Noida International Airport has significantly boosted property value. 3 BHKs along the Noida Expressway and Yamuna Expressway currently show the highest potential for capital appreciation.','2026-02-23 10:19:56','2026-02-23 10:19:56'),(244,62,'What should I check in a 3 BHK floor plan?','Prioritize the Carpet Area (actual usable space) over the Super Area. Ensure the layout has at least two open sides for cross-ventilation and a dedicated utility balcony for laundry.','2026-02-23 10:20:19','2026-02-23 10:20:19'),(245,62,'What is the \"Gold Standard\" size for a 3 BHK in Noida?','For a comfortable family lifestyle, look for a built-up area of 1,350-1,850 sq. ft. In 2026, the best layouts prioritize a 900–1,200 sq. ft. Carpet Area (actual usable space) while minimizing long corridors to maximize room sizes.','2026-02-23 10:20:38','2026-02-23 10:20:38'),(246,62,'How do I verify the legal status of a project?','Search the project’s registration number on the UP-RERA website. Always confirm the builder has obtained the Occupancy Certificate (OC) and cleared all land dues with the Noida Authority before purchase.','2026-02-23 10:20:52','2026-02-23 10:20:52');
